---
const steps = [
  {
    title: "Describe it",
    cmd: "/spec-draft",
    what: "Tell it what you want to build. It interviews you and writes a plain-language spec — what the app does and how people use it.",
  },
  {
    title: "Refine it",
    cmd: "/spec-refine",
    what: "It asks questions, fills the gaps, and chooses the right tools for the job, so the plan is solid before any code is written.",
  },
  {
    title: "Break it down",
    cmd: "/spec-phases",
    what: "It splits the work into small, ordered phases — bite-sized pieces you can follow one at a time.",
  },
  {
    title: "Plan each phase",
    cmd: "/spec-plan",
    what: "It writes a short plan for every phase up front, so nothing is a surprise and you always know what’s next.",
  },
  {
    title: "Build it",
    cmd: "/spec-implement",
    what: "It builds one phase at a time and keeps the spec up to date as it goes, so the plan always matches the app.",
  },
];
---

<section id="how-it-works" class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-14 sm:py-20">
  <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight sm:text-3xl">How it works</h2>
  <p class="mt-3 max-w-xl text-pretty leading-relaxed text-ink-soft">
    Five simple steps take you from an idea to a working app. You stay in plain
    language the whole way — the commands do the technical work.
  </p>

  <ol class="mt-12">
    {
      steps.map((s, i) => (
        <li class="relative grid grid-cols-[2.5rem_1fr] gap-x-5 pb-9 last:pb-0">
          {i < steps.length - 1 && (
            <span
              aria-hidden="true"
              class="absolute left-5 top-11 bottom-1 w-px -translate-x-1/2 bg-line"
            />
          )}
          <span class="z-10 flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-accent text-base font-semibold text-accent-ink">
            {i + 1}
          </span>
          <div class="pt-1">
            <div class="flex flex-wrap items-baseline gap-x-3 gap-y-1">
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink">{s.title}</h3>
              <code class="font-mono text-sm text-ink-soft">{s.cmd}</code>
            </div>
            <p class="mt-2 max-w-lg text-pretty leading-relaxed text-ink-soft">
              {s.what}
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
      ))
    }
  </ol>

  <p class="mt-10 max-w-xl text-pretty leading-relaxed text-ink-soft">
    Each step runs in a fresh session, and the spec is always kept current — so
    the AI never loses track of what you’re building.
  </p>

  <!-- bonus step — visually distinct (dashed/tinted) to signal it's optional -->
  <div class="mt-12 grid grid-cols-[2.5rem_1fr] gap-x-5">
    <span
      class="flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-full border-2 border-dashed border-accent text-lg text-accent"
      aria-hidden="true">★</span
    >
    <div
      class="rounded-2xl border border-dashed border-accent-soft-line bg-accent-soft/60 p-5 sm:p-6"
    >
      <div class="flex flex-wrap items-baseline gap-x-3 gap-y-1">
        <span
          class="rounded-full bg-accent px-2 py-0.5 text-[0.7rem] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-accent-ink"
          >Bonus</span
        >
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink">Make it beautiful</h3>
      </div>
      <p class="mt-2 max-w-lg text-pretty leading-relaxed text-ink-soft">
        Vibe-Spec gets the foundation right — solid, working, production-grade.
        When you want it to <em class="font-medium not-italic text-ink"
          >look</em
        > as good as it works, hand it to
        <a
          href="https://impeccable.style"
          class="font-medium text-ink underline decoration-accent-soft-line underline-offset-4 transition-colors hover:decoration-accent"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer">impeccable</a
        > — a separate set of design skills (<code class="font-mono text-sm"
          >/polish</code
        >, <code class="font-mono text-sm">/bolder</code>, <code
          class="font-mono text-sm">/delight</code
        >) that turn a working app into a beautiful one. This very site was built
        that way.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
